Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Quarter the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan on medium-high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the mushrooms to the bacon, stirring occasionally until golden all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @Worcester sauce{22%ml} to the mushrooms and allow it to evaporate, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, cook for ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount).

Stir in the lentils, then bring the mixture to the boil. Simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g} and pop it in a #small bowl{} with the @Dijon mustard{10%g} (add less if you don't love mustard) and @creme fraiche{150%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir together and set aside.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @?butter{knob}(if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Taste the lentil and bacon filling and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and top with an even layer of mash. Spoon the cheese and mustard mixture over the mash and spread it out with the back of a #spoon.

Bake the pie on the top shelf of your #oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Pop the dish on a #baking tray{} to catch any drips.

When your Welsh rarebit pie is ready, remove from the #oven and allow to stand for ~{2%minutes} before serving.

Spoon generously onto your plates and dig in. Enjoy!